## 🧪 Phase 2: Scenario Generation

### Step 2.1 — Scenario Coverage Rules

For EVERY component discovered, generate Gherkin scenarios covering:

|Category                |Must Cover                                      |
|------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
|**Navigation**          |Route loads, URL is correct, page title visible |
|**Initial State**       |Default content rendered, loading states        |
|**Happy Path**          |Primary user workflow succeeds end-to-end       |
|**Form Validation**     |Required fields, invalid input, error messages  |
|**Form Submission**     |Success response, failure/error response        |
|**CRUD Operations**     |Create, Read, Update, Delete if applicable      |
|**Permissions**         |Auth-guarded routes reject unauthenticated users|
|**Empty State**         |No data scenario renders correctly              |
|**Pagination/Filtering**|Tables with sorting, filtering, paging          |
|**Modals/Dialogs**      |Open, confirm, cancel, close on success         |
|**Negative Cases**      |Server errors (500), not found (404)            |
|**Accessibility**       |Keyboard navigation, ARIA labels present        |

### Step 2.2 — Feature File Format

```gherkin
# e2e/features/<module>/<module>.feature
# ⚠️ USER NOTE: You may add new scenarios below any existing ones.
# Follow the same Given/When/Then pattern. Tags are optional.
# Do NOT modify step text that already has a step definition.

@<module>
Feature: <Module Display Name>
  As a [user role]
  I want to [action]
  So that [business value]

  Background:
    Given the user is authenticated
    And the user navigates to "/<route>"

  # ──────────────────────────────────────────
  # HAPPY PATH
  # ──────────────────────────────────────────

  @smoke @happy-path
  Scenario: Page loads with correct title
    Then the page title should be "<Title>"
    And the "<module>-container" element should be visible

  @happy-path
  Scenario: User successfully creates a <entity>
    When the user clicks the "Add <Entity>" button
    And the user fills in the "<entity>" form with valid data
    And the user submits the form
    Then a success notification should appear
    And the new <entity> should appear in the list

  # ──────────────────────────────────────────
  # VALIDATION
  # ──────────────────────────────────────────

  @validation
  Scenario: Required fields show errors on empty submit
    When the user clicks the "Add <Entity>" button
    And the user submits the form without filling required fields
    Then validation error messages should be visible for required fields

  @validation
  Scenario Outline: Field-level validation for <field>
    When the user enters "<value>" into the "<field>" field
    And the user blurs the field
    Then the error "<error>" should appear

    Examples:
      | field  | value          | error                        |
      | email  | notanemail     | Please enter a valid email   |
      | phone  | abc            | Phone must be numeric        |

  # ──────────────────────────────────────────
  # ERROR HANDLING
  # ──────────────────────────────────────────

  @error-handling
  Scenario: Server error shows user-friendly message
    Given the API returns a 500 error for "<endpoint>"
    When the user performs the primary action
    Then an error message should be displayed
    And the user should remain on the current page

  # ──────────────────────────────────────────
  # AUTH & PERMISSIONS
  # ──────────────────────────────────────────

  @auth
  Scenario: Unauthenticated user is redirected to login
    Given the user is not authenticated
    When the user navigates to "/<protected-route>"
    Then the user should be redirected to "/login"

  # ──────────────────────────────────────────
  # ✏️ USER-ADDED SCENARIOS (add below this line)
  # ──────────────────────────────────────────
```

