## 🚦 Devin Decision Rules

|Situation                       |Action                                                    |
|--------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------|
|Module not found                |STOP → ask user for correct module name                   |
|No routes found                 |Check `app-routing.module.ts` and all `*.routing.ts` files|
|Angular Material detected       |Use `mat-*` selectors in helpers                          |
|Auth interceptor found          |Add token injection to `auth.helper.ts`                   |
|Existing `e2e/` folder          |Merge, don’t overwrite — append to `.feature` file        |
|Tests fail on first run         |Retry once; if still failing, log details in PR body      |
|`data-testid` attributes missing|Use `getByRole` and `getByLabel` as fallback              |
|GitHub CLI not available        |Print PR URL and body to stdout for manual creation       |

-----

## 📌 Consistency Standards (Always Apply)

- **Selectors priority:** `data-testid` > `aria-label` > `role` > `text` > CSS class
- **Never** use `page.waitForTimeout()` as primary wait strategy — use explicit waits
- **Always** clear fields before filling (`await input.clear()`)
- **Always** wait for Angular to stabilize after navigation
- **Always** use Page Objects — never raw selectors in step definitions
- **Always** tag scenarios: `@smoke`, `@happy-path`, `@validation`, `@error-handling`, `@auth`
- **Feature files are user-editable** — mark clearly with comments where users can add scenarios
- **Step definitions must be generic enough** to be reused across scenarios

